body:
## 🐛 Bug description

Insights middleware sometimes fails to initialize insightsClient before the first event.

[Here](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/master/src/middlewares/createInsightsMiddleware.ts#L41:L41) insights middleware checks if `insightsClient` is initialized (asynchronously). If not, it initializes it. However this asynchronous task may not end before the first event. Then the insights middleware tries to send the first event with `insightsClient`, `insightsClient` will throw an error:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/499898/96729283-46a29300-13b5-11eb-955f-efc52b6ad4c5.png)

## How to solve

The most straightforward solution to this problem is to initialize the client without checking if it's already initialized. Then everything will be synchronous. It leaves us a concern which I had in the first place.
> What if `insightsClient` is already initialized?

Naively thinking, it should be fine. According to our documentation, users are not supposed to initialize it on their own (We don't even mention `init`.)
However what if they somehow initialize it? It's actually okay. It will re-assign some variables. No problem.

We could update `search-insights` to accept an option like `ignoreIfAlreadyInitialized`, but it doesn't seem necessary.

So, my suggestion would be to replace 

```js
    insightsClient('_get', '_hasCredentials', (hasCredentials: boolean) => {
      if (!hasCredentials) {
        const [appId, apiKey] = getAppIdAndApiKey(instantSearchInstance.client);
        insightsClient('_get', '_userToken', (userToken: string) => {
          warning(
            !userToken,
            `You set userToken before \`createInsightsMiddleware()\` and it is ignored.
Please set the token after the \`createInsightsMiddleware()\` call.
createInsightsMiddleware({ /* ... */ });
insightsClient('setUserToken', 'your-user-token');
// or
aa('setUserToken', 'your-user-token');
            `
          );
        });
        insightsClient('init', { appId, apiKey });
      }
    });
```

with

```js
        const [appId, apiKey] = getAppIdAndApiKey(instantSearchInstance.client);
        insightsClient('_get', '_userToken', (userToken: string) => {
          warning(
            !userToken,
            `You set userToken before \`createInsightsMiddleware()\` and it is ignored.
Please set the token after the \`createInsightsMiddleware()\` call.
createInsightsMiddleware({ /* ... */ });
insightsClient('setUserToken', 'your-user-token');
// or
aa('setUserToken', 'your-user-token');
            `
          );
        });
        insightsClient('init', { appId, apiKey });
```

What do you think?
